\begin{theorem}\label{main1}
    Suppose that a modal sentence $A$ is not valid in a conversely well-founded finite Kripke model. 
    Then, there exists a $\Sigma_2$ formula $\tau(x)$ weakly representing $T$ in $\PA$ and an arithmetical interpretation $f$ based on $\PR_\tau(x)$ such that $T \nvdash f(A)$. 
\end{theorem}

